# Agility CLI - Cursor Rules

## Manifest-Driven Development (MANDATORY)
- ALWAYS check .cursor/manifest.md at start of development sessions
- ALWAYS reference manifest for project status questions
- ALWAYS update manifest when adding/changing tasks
- ALWAYS archive completed phases to changelog.md

## Chain Assembly Standards (MANDATORY)
- ALWAYS check .cursor/chain-assembly.md before building chain-related features
- NEVER build custom chain assembly logic - use established services
- ALWAYS use SourceDataLoader for data loading operations
- ALWAYS import from src/lib/services/sync-analysis/ for chain operations
- NEVER reinvent dependency relationship building
- ALWAYS follow the 6-step analysis framework

## Development Protocol
1. Read current manifest status
2. Plan work in manifest before executing
3. Update progress markers as work completes
4. **ASK USER to verify functionality before marking complete**
5. **GET USER APPROVAL before committing**
6. Use manifest task IDs in commit messages

## Code Quality
- No `any` types - use proper TypeScript typing
- Search for existing types before creating new ones
- Use keytar for token storage, never file-based
- Test with real instance data (guid: 13a8b394-u)

## Commit Protocol
- NEVER commit without user approval
- NEVER mark tasks complete without user verification
- ASK user to test functionality before committing
- Only commit after user confirms feature works as expected

## File Organization
- Pull logic: use lib/downloaders/
- Analysis logic: use lib/services/dependency-analyzer.ts
- Chain operations: use lib/services/sync-analysis/
- UI prompts: use lib/prompts/
- Document quirks in .cursor/gotchas.md
- Log failed approaches in .cursor/failed-approaches.md 